channel.title: Got some ol' compiler errors i cannot fix for the life of me
channel.description:
Hey, so first off.. I was playing around in my src\com\rs\game folder, trying to get rid of some of the things i accidentally changed that i shouldnt have.. When i had like 8 errors in my source's compiler.. So i couldnt fix them so i just got the source files that i downloaded first off and just replaced the ones showing errors, and now here is some errors that come up.. Im not to sure why they are there, they are the exact same files as were there when i first downloaded and they didnt show any errors then..
[code]Note: src\com\rs\game\player\Inventory.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. compiled Player folder Note: src\com\rs\game\player\Inventory.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. compiled Server folder Note: src\com\rs\game\player\Inventory.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. compiling Dialogues Note: src\com\rs\game\player\Inventory.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. compiled Main Server Folder Note: src\com\rs\game\player\Inventory.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. compiled Main Server Folder Note: src\com\rs\game\player\Inventory.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. Compiled all Successfully Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
And also, in my client side, I get these errors when i compile. Not sure how to fix here either.
[code]src\Class381.java:20: warning: non-varargs call of varargs method with inexact a rgument type for last parameter; Method method = var_class.getDeclaredMethod("get PlatformMBeanServer", null);
^ cast to Class for a varargs call cast to Class[] for a non-varargs call and to suppress this warning src\Class381.java:21: warning: non-varargs call of varargs method with inexact a rgument type for last parameter; Object object = method.invoke(null, null); ^ cast to Object for a varargs call cast to Object[] for a non-varargs call and to suppress this warning Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 2 warnings src\Class381.java:20: warning: non-varargs call of varargs method with inexact a rgument type for last parameter; Method method = var_class.getDeclaredMethod("get PlatformMBeanServer", null);
^ cast to Class for a varargs call cast to Class[] for a non-varargs call and to suppress this warning src\Class381.java:21: warning: non-varargs call of varargs method with inexact a rgument type for last parameter; Object object = method.invoke(null, null); ^ cast to Object for a varargs call cast to Object[] for a non-varargs call and to suppress this warning Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 2 warnings Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Any help on either of the two would be greatly appreciated! Thanks a bunch.
EDIT: I realised that none of those are actually errors, the first one said "compiled succesfully" and the second are just warnings... I have also portforwarded and made a jar file for my client and downloaded it on my other computer but when i changed the ip in the source the compiler didnt work so that is probably why i couldnt connect on my computer downstairs.. But does it matter if the compilers say warning and show the stuff even tho they arent errors?
Thanks again.

item.title: Got some ol' compiler errors i cannot fix for the life of me
item.dc:creator: @pure2ownage Pure_
item.description:
@pure2ownage wrote:

Warnings are just pointers to possible issues I doubt they will matter in your case. I think it’s always import to fix as much of them as possible though. Your code should run without fault though, good job!

item.title: Got some ol' compiler errors i cannot fix for the life of me
item.dc:creator: @adamgulka adamgulka
item.description:
@adamgulka wrote:

Pure_:

It doesn’t matter in most cases, as for the second if the parameter is varargs don’t send null values, ie trim the null parameters at the end. As for the first you can just suppress those or deal with them as you see fit.

Ok, so I got rid of the null’s that were causing the errors… this is all I get now.

Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. Press any key to continue . . .

And thats for the second one. The first one i didnt do anything, because there are no errors, so I think it works to compile.

So basically im asking if the code I just posted is good? and same with the first one in he main post.
